{"parse":{"title":"butter","pageid":7388,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Butter}}\n==English==\n[[Image:NCI butter.jpg|thumb|right|250 px|A stick of butter {{gloss|food made from cream}} with a [[butter knife]].]]\n{{wp}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|bŭʹtər}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈbʌtəɹ/}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbʌtə/|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-butter.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbʌtɚ/|[ˈbʌɾɚ]|a=GA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-butter.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbatə/|[ˈbaɾə]|a=NZ}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbʌtəɾ/|a=Scotland}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbʊtə/|a=Northern England,Midlands}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbʊhɐ/|a=[[w:Dublin English#Local Dublin English|Local Dublin]]|ref=Hickey, Raymond (1998). Developments and change in Dublin English. Language Change. [https://doi.org/10.1515/9783110807653.209 pp. 11]}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌtə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|but|ter}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{PIE word|en|gʷṓws}}\n{{etymon|en|id=dairy|:inh|enm:buter|tree=1}}\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*tewh₂-}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|buter}}, {{m|enm|butter}}, from {{inh|en|ang|butere}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*buterā}}, from {{der|en|la|būtȳrum}}, from {{der|en|grc|βούτῡρον||cow cheese}}, compound of {{m|grc|βοῦς||ox, cow}} and {{m|grc|τῡρός||cheese}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|nl|boter}} and {{cog|de|Butter}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|en|butta|buttah||slang}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|-|s}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q34172}} {{C|en|Foods}} A soft, fatty foodstuff made by [[churn]]ing the [[cream]] of [[milk]] (generally cow's milk).\n#: {{cot|en|lard|shortening|fat|drippings|renderings|double cream|curdled cream|clotted cream}}\n# {{lb|en|cuisine}} Any of various foodstuffs made from other foods or oils, similar in consistency to, eaten like or intended as a substitute for butter (''preceded by the name of the food used to make it'').\n#: {{cot|en|margarine}}\n#: {{co|en|peanut '''butter'''}}\n#: {{co|en|soy '''butter'''}}\n#: {{co|en|chocolate '''butter'''}}\n# Any of various substances made from other (especially plant-based) oils or fats, used in [[moisturizer]]s, [[cosmetics]], etc.\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2016-09-07|author=Elaine Stavert|title=Beauty Oils & Butter|publisher=GMC PUBLICATIONS LTD|isbn=9781861087126\n|text='''Butters''' such as cocoa, illippe, kokum, mango, murumuru, sal (shorea) and shea occur naturally and are obtained directly from the plant.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2019-04-05|author=Heather A.E. Benson; Michael S. Roberts; Vania Rodrigues Leite-Silva; Kenneth Walters|title=Cosmetic Formulation: Principles and Practice|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=9781482235401|page=227\n|text='''Butters''' are triglycerides {{...|that generally have a titer point between 20°C and 40.5°C, at which the mixture of fatty acids solidifies}}. ''Cocoa '''butter''''' (''Theobroma cacao'') is used as an emollient in topical cosmetic formulations, {{...}} South American and the Brazilian rainforest offer various plants with common '''butters''' used in the industry that include {{...}} cupuaçu '''butter''' {{...}} and murumuru butter from the murumuru palm tree (''Astrocaryum murumuru''). India is another source of many '''butters''' used in cosmetic products, including kokum '''butter''' extracted from the seeds of the ''Garcinia indica'' tree, mango '''butter''' from the ''Mangifera indica'' tree and shea '''butter'''{{nb...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|chemistry}} Any specific [[soft]] [[substance]].\n#: {{co|en|'''butter''' of antimony; '''butter''' of arsenic}}\n# {{lb|en|slang|sometimes|attributive}} Something that is [[smooth]], [[impressive]]{{,}} or [[appealing]]. {{n-g|(Compare {{m|en|smooth as butter}}.)}}<ref>{{R:GDoS|entry=butter|pos=adj|sense=2|id=byn2roi}}</ref>\n#* {{RQ:Twitter|en|date=2024-02-12|handle=OluBliss|id=1756854058827301230|passage=That “{{w|Confessions Part II|Confessions}}” into “{{w|Nice & Slow|Nice and Slow}}” transition {{q-g|at the {{w|Super Bowl LVIII halftime show}}}} was '''buttah''' !}}\n## {{lb|en|aviation|slang}} A smooth plane landing.\n##: {{ux|en|That landing was total '''butter'''!}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|title=Terms derived from ''butter'' (noun)|\n\n|almond-butter\n|apple butter\n|back butter\n|back-butter\n|bean-butter\n|black butter\n|blue butter\n|body butter\n|brandy butter\n|bread and butter\n|bread-and-butter\n|bread-and-butter issue\n|bread-and-butter letter\n|bread-and-butter note\n|bread-and-butter pickle\n|bread and butter pudding\n|bread-and-butter plate\n|budder\n|butterable\n|butter-and-egg money\n|butter bread|movie theater butter\n|butterbird\n|butter board\n|butterburger\n|butterbutt\n|butter cake\n|buttercream\n|buttercrunch\n|butterdock\n|butterer\n|butter flap\n|butterhead\n|butterhorn\n|butterleaf\n|butterlike\n|butter keeper\n|butterman\n|butter measure\n|buttermint\n|buttermonger\n|butteroil\n|butter pat\n|butter plate\n|butterscotch\n|butter scoop\n|butter slime\n|butterspoon\n|butter tofu\n|butterwoman\n|butter yellow\n\n|cacao butter\n|cannabutter\n|clarified butter\n|cocoa butter\n|cowboy butter\n|drawn butter\n|duck butter\n|egg butter\n|fairies' butter\n|fairy butter\n|green butter\n|karite butter\n|kombo butter\n|like butter on a bald monkey\n|lung butter\n|maple butter\n|nonbutter\n|nun's butter\n|nut butter\n|nutter\n|palm-butter\n|peanut butter\n|peanut-butter cup\n|peanut-butter-and-jelly\n|peanut-butter-and-jelly sandwich\n|plant butter\n|print butter\n|process butter\n|rebutter\n|renovated butter\n|rock butter\n|rum butter\n|school-butter\n|shea butter tree\n|shea butter\n|sugar-butter sauce\n|sweet butter\n|vegan butter\n|vegetable butter\n|whatever melts your butter\n|witches' butter\n\n|butter bean|butter brickle|butter clam|butter cream|butter curler|butter dish|butter fat|butter icing|butter muslin|butter of antimony|butter of arsenic|butter of tin|butter of zinc|butter oil|butter paddle|butter paper|butter salt|butter tart|butter-and-egg man|butter-and-eggs|butter-box|butter-fat|butter-fingered|butter-slide|butter-woman\n\n|almond butter|bog butter|brown butter|bull butter|butter bar|butter boat|butter bomb|butter chicken|butterface|butter face|butterfaced|butter fingers|butter flower|butter fruit|butter lamp|butter mochi|butter mountain|butter pear|butter pie|butter tea|butter tooth|butter tree|butter will not melt in someone's mouth|butter won't melt in someone's mouth|butter would not melt in someone's mouth|butter wouldn't melt in someone's mouth|butter-and-egger|butter-muslin|compound butter|cookie butter|Cumberland rum butter|garlic butter|gooey butter cake|guns and butter|head butter|head-butter|herb butter|honey butter|knob of butter|land with one's bum in the butter|like a hot knife through butter|like a knife through butter|maître d' butter|melt someone's butter|midshipman's butter|nut-brown butter|palm butter|pea butter|peanut butter and jelly|peanut butter cup|poor man's butter|put butter on one's bread|smooth as butter|snail butter|snuff-and-butter|tanning butter|truffle butter|whipped butter|whiskey butter|whisky butter|kanya butter\n\n}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{top3}}\n* {{l|en|butterface}}<!--but her-->\n* {{l|en|butterfly}}<!--origin uncertain-->\n* {{l|en|butter-ham}}<!--from Dutch-->\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|tpi|bata}}\n* {{desc|ja|バター|tr=batā|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ko|빠다|bor=1}} {{qualifier|North Korea}}, {{l|ko|버터}} {{qualifier|South Korea}}\n* {{desc|sm|pata|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|si|බටර්|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tl|bater|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|zu|ibhotela|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|soft foodstuff made from milk}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|азеҭ}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|botter}}\n* Ajië: {{tt|aji|dibëë}}\n* Akkadian: {{tt|akk|𒉌𒉣𒈾|tr=ḫimētu}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|gjalpë|m}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|сармай}}, {{tt|alt|сары май}}, {{tt|alt|май}}, {{tt|alt|сарју}}, {{tt|alt|сары јуу}}\n* Alutiiq: {{tt|ems|masla}}\n* American Sign Language: {{tt|ase|H@TipPalm-PalmDown-OpenB@CenterChesthigh-PalmUp Contact H@BasePalm H@TipPalm Contact H@BasePalm H@TipPalm Contact H@BasePalm}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ቅቤ}}\n* Antillean Creole: {{tt|gcf|bè}}\n* Apache:\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|ibeʼ nestʼógi}}\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|ibeʼ nestʼógi}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|زُبْدَة|f}}\n*: Chadian Arabic: {{t|shu|زبدة|f|tr=zibde}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|زبدة|f|tr=zébda}}\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{tt|afb|زبدة|tr=zibda}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|زبدة|f|tr=zibda, zubda}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{tt|ajp|زبدة|f|tr=zibda, zubda}}\n* Aragonese: {{tt|an|manteca|f}}\n* Aramaic: {{tt|arc|כרעא|m|tr=karʽa}}\n*: Classical Syriac: {{tt|syc|ܚܐܘܬܐ|f|tr=ḥeˀwṯā}}, {{tt|syc|ܟܪܥܐ|tr=kərāʿāʾ, kārʿāʾ, karʿāʾ}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|կարագ}}, {{tt+|hy|կոգի}} {{q|archaic}}\n*: Old Armenian: {{tt|xcl|կոգի}}, {{tt|xcl|իւղ}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|umtu|n}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|মাখণ}}, {{tt|as|ননী}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|mantega|f}}\n* Aukan: {{t|djk|botoo}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|yağ}}, {{t|az|kərə yağı}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|май}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|gurin}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|ма́сла|n}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|মাখন}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|amanenn|m}}, {{tt+|br|amann|m}}\n*: Middle Breton: {{tt|xbm|amanen}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|масло́|n}}, {{tt+|bg|ма́сло|n}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ထောပတ်}}\n* Buryat: {{tt|bua|сагаан тоһон}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{t|rue|ма́сло|n}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|mantega|f}}\n* Champenois: {{tt|roa-cha|bure}} {{q|Auve}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|налха}}, {{tt|ce|даьтта}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᎪᏢᏅ}}, {{tt|chr|ᎪᏢᏅᎢ}}\n* Cheyenne: {{tt|chy|heóveamėške}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|牛油}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{t|cdo|牛奶油}}\n*: Hakka: {{tt|hak|牛油|tr=ngiù-yù}}, {{tt|hak|乳油|tr=nen-yù}}, {{tt|hak|白塔|tr=pat-tá}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|牛油|tr=gû-iû}}, {{tt|nan-hbl|bá-tah}} {{q|Taiwan}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|黃油}}, {{tt+|cmn|牛油}}, {{tt+|cmn|白脫}}\n*: Wu: {{tt|wuu|白脫|}}, {{tt|wuu|牛油}}, {{t|wuu|白脫油}}\n* Chuvash: {{tt|cv|ҫу}}\n* Coptic: {{tt|cop|ϭⲉⲗⲓ}} {{q|Bohairic}}; {{tt|cop|ⲥⲁⲓⲣⲉ}} {{q|Sahidic}}\n* Cornish: {{tt|kw|amanyn|m}}\n*: Old Cornish: {{tt|o