alt=pȕter|m}}\n* Seychellois Creole: {{tt|crs|diber}}\n* Shan: {{tt|shn|ထေႃးပၢတ်ႈ}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt|scn|butirru|m}}\n* Sidamo: {{tt|sid|buuro}}\n* Silesian: {{tt|szl|masło|n}}\n* Sindhi: {{tt|sd|مکڻ|tr=makhanu}}; {{q|molten}} {{tt|sd|گيہہ|m|tr=gīhu|alt=گيِہہُ}}\n* Sinhalese: {{tt|si|බටර්}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|maslo|n}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|maslo|n}}, {{tt|sl|puter|m}} {{q|colloquial}}\n* Somali: {{tt+|so|subag|m}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|butra|f}}, {{tt|dsb|masło|n}} {{q|rare}}\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{tt|hsb|butra|f}}\n* Sotho: {{tt+|st|sereledi}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|mantequilla|f}}, {{tt+|es|manteca|f}} {{q|Argentina, Paraguay, Uruguay}}\n*: Old Spanish: {{tt|osp|butiro|m}}, {{tt|osp|buturo|m}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{tt|srn|botro}}\n* Sumerian: {{tt|sux|𒉌|tr=i₃, ia₃}}\n* Sundanese: {{tt+|su|ᮙᮔ᮪ᮒᮦᮌ}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|siagi}}\n* Swazi: {{tt|ss|libhotela|c5}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|smör|n}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|mantekilya}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|маска}}, {{tt+|tg|равған}}, {{tt|tg|равғани зард}}\n* Talysh: {{t|tly|ruyən}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|வெண்ணெய்}}, {{tt+|ta|இழுது}}, {{tt+|ta|விழுது}}\n* Tarantino: {{tt|roa-tar|burre|m}}\n* Tarifit: {{t|rif|trussi|f}}\n* Tatar: {{tt+|tt|май}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|వెన్న}}\n* Tetum: {{tt|tet|manteiga}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|เนย}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|མར།}}, {{tt|bo|གསོལ་མར}} {{q|honorific}}\n* Tigre: {{tt|tig|ዝበድ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{t|ti|ጠስሚ}}\n* Tocharian B: {{tt|txb|kewiye}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{tt|tpi|bata}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|tereyağı}}, {{tt+|tr|yağ}} {{q|obsolete}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{tt|ota|تره‌یاغی|tr=tereyağı}}, {{tt|ota|یاغ|tr=yağ}}, {{t|ota|روغن|tr=revgan, rugan}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|mesge}}\n* Tuvan: {{tt|tyv|саржаг}}, {{tt|tyv|үс}}\n* Udi: {{tt|udi|кӏаракӏ}}\n* Udmurt: {{tt|udm|вӧй}}\n* Ugaritic: {{tt|uga|𐎃𐎎𐎀𐎚|tr=ḫmảt}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|ма́сло|n}}\n* Unami: {{tt|unm|putël|in}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|گھی|m}}, {{tt|ur|مَکَّھن|m}}, {{tt|ur|نَونی|f}}, {{tt|ur|نُونی|f}}, {{tt|ur|نَوَنِیت|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|سېرىق ماي}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|saryogʻ}}, {{tt+|uz|moy}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|uz|сарёғ}}, {{tt+|uz|мой}}\n* Venetan: {{tt+|vec|butiro|m}}, {{tt|vec|botiro|m}}\n* Veps: {{tt|vep|voi}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|bơ}}\n* Vilamovian: {{tt|wym|putter|f}}\n* Vili: {{t|vif|mantèka}}\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|bör}}, {{tt|vo|mileg}} {{q|older term}}\n* Võro: {{tt|vro|võid}}\n* Votic: {{tt|vot|või}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|boure|m}}\n* Waray-Waray: {{tt|war|mantikilya}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|menyn|m}}, {{t+|cy|ymenyn|m}}\n*: Middle Welsh: {{tt|wlm|ymenyn}}\n* West Flemish: {{tt|vls|beuter|m}}\n* Winnebago: {{t|win|hirawaxiri}}\n* Wolaytta: {{t|wal|oyssaa}}\n* Wolof: {{tt|wo|bóor}}, {{tt+|wo|diw}}\n* Xârâcùù: {{tt|ane|dibèè}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|ibhotolo|c9}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|арыы}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|פּוטער|f}}\n* Yola: {{tt|yol|buthther}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|bọta|alt=bọ́tà}}, {{tt|yo|ori|alt=òrí}}\n* Yup'ik: {{tt|esu|masslaaq}}\n* Zealandic: {{tt|zea|beuter}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|naijyouz}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|ibhotela|alt=îbhotêla|c5}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|other foodstuffs like butter}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|май}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|ŝmiraĵo}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|beurre|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|ма́сло|n}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|smör|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Georgian: {{t+check|ka|ერბო}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[spread]] butter on.\n#: {{ux|en|'''Butter''' the toast.}}\n# {{lb|en|skiing|snowboarding}} To move one's weight backwards or forwards onto the tips or tails of one's skis or snowboard so only the tip or tail is in contact with the snow. Similar to applying butter to bread with the end of a knife.\n## To spin on skis or a snowboard using only the tips or tails being in contact with the snow\n#: {{hypo|en|nosebutter|tailbutter}}\n# {{lb|en|slang|obsolete|transitive}} To [[increase]] (stakes) at every [[throw]] of [[dice]], or every [[game]].\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|en|title=Terms derived from ''butter'' (verb)\n|butter one's bread on both sides\n|butter the cony\n|butter up|butter down|butter out\n|fine words butter no parsnips\n|have one's bread buttered for life\n|know which side one's bread is buttered on\n|buttering\n|buttered\n|nosebutter\n|nosebuttering\n|nosebuttered|whatever butters your biscuit|whatever butters your biscuits|whatever butters your bread|whatever butters your muffin|whatever butters your toast\n|tailbutter\n|tailbuttering| butter one's bread and lie in it\n|tailbuttered\n|butter my butt and call it a biscuit|butter my butt and call me a biscuit|butter someone's biscuit}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top-also|to spread butter on|spread|butter}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|botter}}, {{tt|af|bebotter}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|намазвам с масло}}\n* Czech: {{qualifier|[[impf.]]}} {{tt|cs|mazat máslem}}, {{tt|cs|namazat máslem}}, {{qualifier|[[pf.]]}} {{tt|cs|pomazat máslem}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|smøre}} brødet\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|beboteren}}, {{tt|nl|inboteren}}, {{tt|nl|met boter besmeren}}\n* Faroese: {{tt|fo|smyrja}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|voidella}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|beurrer}}\n* German: {{tt|de|[[mit]] [[Butter]] [[bestreichen]]}}\n* Hindi: {{tt|hi|मक्खन लगाना}}, {{tt+|hi|चुपड़ना}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt|is|smyrja}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|butrizar}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|butyrar}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|imburrare}}\n* Marathi: {{tt|mr|माखणे}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|beurrer}} {{qualifier|Jersey}}\n* Polish: {{tt|pl|smarować masłem}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|amanteigar}}, {{tt|pt|[[passar]] [[manteiga]] [[em]]}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|нама́слить}}, {{tt+|ru|нама́сливать}}, {{tt|ru|нама́зать ма́слом}}, {{tt|ru|нама́зывать ма́слом}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|namazati z maslom}}\n* Spanish: {{tt|es|[[untar]] [[con]] [[mantequilla]]}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|bre}}, {{tt+|sv|breda}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|ทาเนย|tr=ta noey}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|[[зма́щувати]] [[масло|ма́слом]]|impf}}, {{t|uk|[[змасти́ти]] [[масло|ма́слом]]|pf}}\n* Vietnamese: {{qualifier|vào}} {{tt|vi|quẹt bơ}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|en|butyraceous}}\n* {{l|en|ghee}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{ety|en|id=butt|:af|butt|-er<id:agent noun>|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# Someone or something that [[butt]]s.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2005|author=David E. Fastovsky; David B. Weishampel|title=The Evolution and Extinction of the Dinosaurs|page=156\n|passage={{...}} these animals lacked self-correcting mechanisms of the kind seen in modern head-'''butters''' such as goats and big-horn sheep that would have kept the tremendous forces aligned with the rest of the skeleton.}}\n# Someone or something that [[butt in|butts in]]; a [[busybody]].\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n{{topics|en|Condiments|Dairy products|Fats and oils}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{m|fr|butte}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-butter.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-butter.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-butter.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{fr-verb}}\n\n# to [[heap]]\n#: {{ux|fr|'''butter''' les pommes de terre.|'''to heap''' the potatoes [onto something].}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{fr-conj-auto}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==German==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|de|De-butter.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|de|verb form}}\n\n# {{verb form of|de|buttern||1|s|pres|;|s|imp}}\n\n==Lombard==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe|lmo}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|lmo|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|butter}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|buter}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Adjective===\n{{sv-adj|buttra}}\n\n# [[grumpy]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-adj-reg|3=buttr}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|sv|a=berttu|brutet|buttre}}\n\n{{C|sv|Personality}}\n\n==West Flemish==\n\n===Noun===\n{{vls-noun}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|vls|beuter}}"}}